      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): add qwen3.7-max, qwen3.7-plus, minimax-m3 to provider catalog",
        "body": "## Summary\nThis PR adds missing OpenCode Go provider catalog entries and implements tiered pricing for Qwen Plus models to ensure accurate cost estimation for long-context requests.\n\n### Changes\n- **New Models**: Added `minimax-m3`, `qwen3.7-max`, and `qwen3.7-plus` to the static provider catalog.\n- **Cost Accuracy**: Implemented `tieredPricing` for `qwen3.7-plus` and `qwen3.6-plus` to align with official OpenCode Go pricing (split at 256K tokens).\n- **Verification**: Added focused test cases in `extensions/opencode-go/index.test.ts` to verify cost calculations at the 256K boundary.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Run 1: qwen3.7-plus Cost Tier Transition\n- **behavior:** Verify that `qwen3.7-plus` correctly transitions from Tier 1 (<=256k) to Tier 2 (>256k) pricing in the OpenClaw cost estimation logic.\n- **environment:** Windows 10 Pro, Node.js v24.14.1, OpenClaw Local Workspace.\n- **steps:**\n  1. Patch `extensions/opencode-go/provider-catalog.ts` with `tieredPricing` metadata.\n  2. Run a verification script calling `estimateUsageCost` with 300,000 input tokens.\n  3. Compare `flatCost` (fallback) vs `tieredCost` (actual).\n- **evidence:**\n```json\n{\n  model: opencode-go/qwen3.7-plus,\n  contextWindow: 1000000,\n  flatCost: 0.123,\n  tieredCost: 0.369,\n  tieredPricing: [\n    { input: 0.4, output: 1.6, cacheRead: 0.04, cacheWrite: 0.5, range: [0, 256000] },\n    { input: 1.2, output: 4.8, cacheRead: 0.12, cacheWrite: 1.5, range: [256000, null] }\n  ]\n}\n```\n- **observedResult:** The `tieredCost` (0.369) is significantly higher than the `flatCost` (0.123), confirming that the >256k pricing tier is correctly applied.\n- **notTested:** Actual API request billing was not verified; only the local `estimateUsageCost` logic was tested.\n\nAll unit tests in `extensions/opencode-go/index.test.ts` passed.",
